Package interfaces

Interface IDoctorService

All Known Implementing Classes:
DoctorService
public interface IDoctorService
Interface for doctor-related service operations. Provides methods to manage doctor details, handle appointment requests, manage availability, and update patient records such as diagnoses and prescriptions.

  • Method Details

    • getDoctorById

      Doctor getDoctorById(String hospitalID)
      Retrieves the details of a doctor by their hospital ID.
      Parameters:
      hospitalID - The unique ID of the doctor.
      Returns:
      The Doctor object if found, or null if no doctor exists with the given ID.

    • updateDoctorContact

      boolean updateDoctorContact(String hospitalID, String newContactInformation)
      Updates the contact information of a doctor.
      Parameters:
      hospitalID - The unique ID of the doctor.
      newContactInformation - The new contact information to be updated.
      Returns:
      true if the contact information was successfully updated, false otherwise.

    • listAllDoctors

      void listAllDoctors()
      Lists all the doctors in the system. This typically displays the details of all doctors.

    • setAvailablity

      boolean setAvailablity(Doctor doctor, String dateStr, String timeSlotStr)
      Sets the availability of a doctor for a specific date and time slot.
      Parameters:
      doctor - The Doctor object whose availability is being updated.
      dateStr - The date for which availability is being set, in the format "yyyy-MM-dd".
      timeSlotStr - The time slot for which availability is being set, in the format "HH:mm".
      Returns:
      true if availability was successfully updated, false otherwise.

    • setUnavailability

      boolean setUnavailability(Doctor doctor, String dateStr, String timeSlotStr)
      Sets the unavailability of a doctor for a specific date and time slot.
      Parameters:
      doctor - The Doctor object whose availability is being updated.
      dateStr - The date for which unavailability is being set, in the format "yyyy-MM-dd".
      timeSlotStr - The time slot for which unavailability is being set, in the format "HH:mm".
      Returns:
      true if unavailability was successfully updated, false otherwise.

    • recordAppointmentOutcome

      void recordAppointmentOutcome(String appointmentId, String serviceProvided, String medicationsInput, String quantitiesInput, String consultationNotes)
      Records the outcome of a completed appointment, including services provided, prescribed medications, and consultation notes.
      Parameters:
      appointmentId - The ID of the appointment whose outcome is being recorded.
      serviceProvided - A description of the service provided during the appointment.
      medicationsInput - A list of medications prescribed during the appointment, as a string.
      quantitiesInput - A list of quantities corresponding to the prescribed medications, as a string.
      consultationNotes - Notes recorded during the consultation.
